criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1. signed informed consent, and date;
2. age 18-70 years; diffuse vascular disease;
3. refractory tissue ulceration;
4. can not tolerate revascularization or  interventional surgery.

criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1. highly allergic or who have history of severe allergies; 
2. with shock or systemic failure, abnormal vital signs, and cannot cooperate; 
3. advanced cancer; 
4. severe systemic infections or local infection can not be controlled; 
5. Disfunction of heart, lung, liver, kidney and other vital organs; 
6. leukemia and other serious blood diseases; 
7. positive serological tests such as AIDS, hepatitis B, syphilis, etc.; 
8. deficiency of chromosomes or Gene and immune deficiency; 
9. the patients whose expectations are too high, or do not meet the practical requirements and refused to sign the informed consent.
